wikipedia_page.main: Eric Chisnall (born 5 July 1946) is an English former professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1960s, 1970s and 1980. He played at representative level for Great Britain and England, and at club level for St Helens and Leigh, as a prop or second-row, i.e. number 8 or 10, or, 11 or 12, during the era of contested scrums.
